The paper discusses a text categorization approach that leverages the Tsetlin Machine, which is a machine learning technique. This makes it likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computational linguistics (cs.CL), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper focuses on medical applications, which suggests it could also belong to the sub-categories of information retrieval (cs.IR) and cybernetics (cs.CY).
